OL,3,CBritain's forced adoption scandal: Why
OL,4,Cwon't the government say sorry?
OL,6,FOther countries where forced adoption
OL,7,Ftook place, including Canada,
OL,8,FAustralia, Ireland, Scotland and Wales
OL,9,Fhave already issued a formal apology,
OL,10,Fand in some cases set up redress
OL,11,Fschemes. Westminster has done nothing.
OL,13,FDuring an interview with ITV News, I
OL,14,Fput that point to the Minister for
OL,15,FChildren and Families, Janet Daby MP,
OL,16,Fwho said it's "under review".
OL,18,F"There isn't a reluctance to
OL,19,Fapologise, there's still communication
OL,20,Ftaking place, it's still being looked
OL,21,Fat," she said.
