OL,3,CBritain's forced adoption scandal: Why
OL,4,Cwon't the government say sorry?
OL,6,FJanet Daby, Minister for Children and
OL,7,FFamilies, told ITV News Social Affairs
OL,8,FCorrespondent Sarah Corker that the
OL,9,Fgovernment's response to historic
OL,10,Fforced adoptions is 'under review'
OL,12,FJacqui Adams, 63, was a teenager when
OL,13,Fone day everything changed.
OL,15,F"When I was 17 my mother died. No
OL,16,Fbrothers, sisters, no grandparents, no
OL,17,Faunts, uncles, nobody else," she told
OL,18,FITV News.
