OL,3,CBritain's forced adoption scandal: Why
OL,4,Cwon't the government say sorry?
OL,6,FBetween 1949 and 1976, an estimated
OL,7,F200,000 women were sent away to mother
OL,8,Fand baby institutions run by the
OL,9,Fchurch and state - places of shame and
OL,10,Fsecrecy.
OL,12,FThe adoptions were often handled by
OL,13,Freligious organisations.
OL,15,F"I don't have an identity. I can't
OL,16,Fbuild proper relationships with
OL,17,Fpeople, because you don't trust
OL,18,Fanyone," Ms Adams said.
OL,20,FShe told me an apology is "imperative"
OL,21,Fbut added it is "just the beginning".
